						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I. Year 37: A.D. 944.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged in the middle. Provides a grant of seventy(?) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañcus</hi> of gold for feeding one <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇa</hi>, well versed in Vedas in the temple at Tiruvāṉaikkaṟ Perumāṉaḍigaḷ at Tiruveḷḷaṟai. The temple authorities <hi rend="italic">(mūlapariḍaiyār)</hi> agreed to feed him with cooked rice, dhall, vegetables, ghee, curd and betel leaves.</p>						

						</summary>
